FBIS3-54994 "drsov003_s_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 Georgia Tbilisi Commander Says Tougher Curfew Needed LD0401212094 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1900 GMT 4 Jan 94 LD0401212094 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network Language: Georgian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Koba Kobaidze, a journalist, is here in our studio. [Kobaidze] I welcome you again, dear radio listeners. You are well aware that, by a decision of the city commandant's office, the curfew was lifted in Tbilisi on 1 and 2 January. Commandant Zaza Chachua will speak about the results of this move. [Begin recording] [Chachua] People kept shooting and walking in the streets. There were road accidents and other things. [Kobaidze] What can you envisage in the long run? [Chachua] In the long run? The curfew must become as strict as possible and the administrative bodies must handle everything more firmly. [passage omitted] [Kobaidze] How long do you think Tbilisi will need a curfew? [Chachua] Some more months. At least six months I think. This is the least. [passage omitted, new year greetings and wishes] [end recording]
